# Test API FinTrack avec Authentification

## 1. Créer un utilisateur
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Test User"
}

###

## 2. Se connecter
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

## 3. Créer un compte (nécessite un token JWT)
POST http://localhost:3000/accounts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Mon compte principal",
  "balance": 1000
}

###

## 4. Mettre à jour un compte (nécessite un token JWT)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/accounts/ACCOUNT_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Compte modifié",
  "balance": 2500
}